=== TASK ===
# Transactions & Categorization

## Overview
You are building the LifeOps Finance module’s Transactions & Categorization page. This page enables users to load, view, and manage financial transactions, manually categorize items, create and test categorization rules, and mark exceptions. It serves as the front line for Finance Automation features (ingestion, automated categorization, subscription management, anomaly detection, forecasting, and monthly close workflows) and feeds into the Finance Dashboard (categorized transactions, subscriptions, anomalies, forecasting, monthly close checklist, and agent spend optimization recommendations). The UI must be performant, typed, accessible, and resilient to null/undefined data. All data access should be guarded with null-safety patterns, and the codebase should strictly adhere to the runtime safety constraints listed in the “Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety” section.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Transactions & Categorization page is the primary interface for listing raw and enriched transactions, applying manual categorization, configuring categorization rules (patterns, mappings, and priorities), and flagging or resolving exceptions.
- It acts as a hub between ingestion, categorization automation, and reconciliation workflows. Every manual action should be traceable with an audit trail and reversible where appropriate.

Goals:
- Provide a comprehensive, fast, and reliable workflow for transaction handling:
  - Ingest and display transactions (with enrichment data such as inferred category, confidence, subscription indicators, merchant metadata).
  - Allow manual categorization (reassign category, subcategory) and bulk categorization actions.
  - Create, edit, test, and preview categorization rules (e.g., if merchant matches X and amount > Y then category = Z).
  - Mark exceptions for transactions that cannot be categorized automatically with notes and reasons.
  - Support match & reconcile tooling to align transactions with invoices/subscriptions.
  - Expose actions that integrate with Finance Automation: trigger re-categorization runs, schedule ingestions, push for anomaly review, and flag for monthly close readiness.

Connected features and UI guidelines:
- Ingestion status indicators and recent ingestion logs
- Categorization Rules editor with live preview against the current transaction set
- Bulk Actions toolbar: Categorize, Export, Flag for Review, Add Note
- Match & Reconcile tools to link transactions to subscriptions or invoices
- Visual distinction between auto-categorized vs. manually categorized items
- Audit trail panel showing action history, actor, timestamp, and rationale
- API integrations for ingestion pipelines, categorization services, and reconciliation endpoints (mockable in dev)
- Data visualizations (in the Dashboard) draw from the same canonical data, ensuring consistency

UI/UX guidance:
- Visual emphasis on quick scanning, powerful filtering, and batch operations
- Clear affordances for undo/redo where applicable and explicit confirmation prompts for destructive actions
- Consistent with LifeOps design system: dark UI, dense information, high-contrast action cues, and accessible typography

